comments.body:
There does not appear to be a deadlock here and these threads look normal to me.  Your threads are RUNNABLE and WAITING.  

What kind of problems are you having?
The thread seems waiting for lock forever, and dont recv message anymore.

Can you attach a file with the full thread dump (run jstack with -l for all the locking info)?  As I said in the first post, I don't see a deadlock just from the 2 threads you posted but maybe the full stack trace will show something in more detail.

I see the first thread waiting on the MutexTransport lock which the RUNNABLE thread does seem to have acquired as both threads use the MutextTransport.  However, just because the one thread is WAITING on the lock doesn't necessarily mean there is a deadlock as the other thread appears to be doing work it hasn't finished. (writing to the socket)

Are you able to reproduce your issue of not receiving messages reliably (maybe in a test case)? Also, can you test against 5.11.1 or even 5.12-SNAPSHOT?

Thank you very much, I cannot try 5.11.1 because of it's in production env.
